article.headline: Duquesne 93, Fordham 56
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Elijah Palmer scored 22 points as Duquesne snapped a five-game losing streak and beat Fordham 93-56 on Wednesday night. Duquesne (10-15, 5-9 Atlantic 10) held Fordham (5-19, 2-11) to one field goal over a 8:43 span in the first half. That fueled the 31-4 run that gave Duquesne a 38-14 lead with 7:32 left in the half. The Dukes led 50-25 at halftime. Fordham committed 26 turnovers, which led to 41 points for Duquesne. Duquesne had the rebounding edge at 45 to 32 and held Fordham to just 33.3 percent (17-49) from the floor. Jimmy Tricco hit five 3-pointers for 15 points for the Dukes. Bryant McAllister scored 13 points and Kieron Achara had his fourth straight game in double figures with 11 points. Jack Higgins added 10 points Duquesne. Michael Haynes led Fordham with 14 points. Derrick Breland scored 13 points. Domenic Osei, with 11, and Drew Williamson, with 10, were the other Rams in double figures.
